    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "Redescription of Ve r t i g o (Vertigo) nitidula (Mousson, 1876) (Gastropoda: Vertiginidae) from the Caucasus region" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.287228>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8387550>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.287229> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.287228>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Vertigo spp., shells. A – O. Vertigo (Vertigo) nitidula (Mousson). A. Georgia: Tabatsquri (syntype of P. pygmaea var. nitidula ZMZ 514689). B. Georgia, Tabatsquri (syntype of P. sieversi SMF 2129). C. Georgia, Manglisi (syntype of P. sieversi var. punctum SMF 2125). D. Georgia, Kazbek (syntype of P. sieversi var. subalpestris SMF 2122). E. Georgia, Abastumani (syntype of P. substriata var. mitis SMF 2282). F – G. Georgia, Kobi (ZIN 27). H – J. Russia, lower Adylsu valley (ZMH 80612). K – O. Armenia, Tsaghkadzor, Mount Teghenis (ZMH 80614). P – V. Vertigo (Vertigo) substriata (Jeffreys). P. Germany, Nübel (ZMH 60278); Q. Russia, Zilairskoe plateau, Novoaleksandrovka (ZMH 96098). R. Russia, Altai Republic, 2 km W of Zaisanskaya Elan (ZMH 96096). S. Russia, Chegem valley (ZIN 96). T – V. Georgia, Kobi (ZIN 95). Scale bar = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/287228/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8387550>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Variation in shell size and shape of Vertigo (Vertigo) nitidula (Mousson)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8387550/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.287229>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Distribution of Vertigo (Vertigo) nitidula (Mousson) (dots) and Vertigo (Vertigo) substriata (Jeffreys) (stars) in the Caucasus region (0.5 ° grid)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/287229/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

